<title>ARGENTINA: World Bank asks Argentine province to trim 4,000 jobs.</title>
<headline>World Bank asks Argentine province to trim 4,000 jobs.</headline>
<dateline>BUENOS AIRES 1997-05-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>The World Bank (WB) asked Argentina's northern Salta province to trim an additional 4,000 public jobs as a condition to grant it a $60 million loan, private agency DyN reported Wednesday.</p>
<p>&quot;Payroll cost control is crucial for the province's fiscal recovery,&quot; said a the WB in letter sent to Salta's government in December and made public now in a congressional hearing.</p>
<p>The provincial government has already cut 4,000 jobs but the WB advises it to trim another 4,000, or 10 percent of the current payroll, by means of early retirement, reacommodation and lay-offs, DyN said.</p>
<p>((--Guillermo Haskel, Buenos Aires Newsroom, 541 318-0650))</p>
